data.content:
## Breaking Changes in Microsoft.OpenApi 2.0 (used by ASP.NET Core OpenApi 10.0)

The underlying library upgraded from **OpenAPI.NET v1 → v2**, which aligns with OpenAPI 3.1. Here are the key changes:

### 1. `OpenApiAny` types removed (`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc.)
Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` instead:

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After (.NET 10)
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

Add `using System.Text.Json.Nodes;` and remove `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;`.

### 2. References use dedicated reference types
`OpenApiSecurityScheme` with a `Reference` property is replaced by `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`:

```csharp
// Before
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// After
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};
```

### 3. `Nullable` property removed
OpenAPI 3.1 represents nullability via the `Type` flags (a `[Flags]` enum `JsonSchemaType`):

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After — remove Null from the type flags
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

(To *add* nullability: `property.Value.Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null;`)

---

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of namespace changes
| Remove | Add |
|--------|-----|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `System.Text.Json.Nodes` |

The `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models` namespace still provides `OpenApiResponse`, `OpenApiSecurityRequirement`, `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`, and `JsonSchemaType`.
